node.text: Alison and I stopped in La Jolla this past weekend after picking up my new torch and ventured over to the cove! It was really cool to see the sea lions up close and see so many people snorkeling and scuba diving! We couldn’t believe we forgot our swim suits.. Just gives us an excuse to go back, I guess 😎 I managed to snag a quick photo of this pomegranate/green amber purple montage cap while we were at the cove. Message me if you wanna scoop it! ALSO! I have something fun to show you all tomorrow! Stay tuned 👀🥰 #lajolla #carbcap #montage #bubblecap

In his interview, we learn about his “chip stack” technique of using his custom millies to create the most vibrant pieces of functional glass art in the glass blowing game.
